    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-06T18:03:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-06T18:03:00-05:00" n="444"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/4–653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d444fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_YKT1">Young</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_TW1"
                            >Treumann</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-06T18:03:00-05:00"
                            >April 6, 1953—6:03 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>624. Department distribution only. <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> in C
                    61736 April 4<note n="2" xml:id="d444fn2">Not printed. (<persName
                            corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413)</note> has
                    informed Department Army (1) serious consequences US and UN could result from
                    active opposition <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government to further
                    armistice negotiations or agreements (2) possible course action their part could
                    include (a) withdrawal <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> representatives
                        <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> armistice delegation or (b) at worst
                    attempt withdraw elements <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Army from UN
                    control and remove <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government officials from
                    UN influence (3) plans at hand to meet emergency arising from latter contingency
                    and all probable contingencies are under continuing study. <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> recommends <pb facs="0913" n="879"
                        xml:id="pg_879"/> State take appropriate action influence <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government conform UN actions.</p>
                <p>Department considering joint State–Defense telegram <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1"
                        >CINCUNC</gloss> requesting close Embassy-<gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1"
                        >CINCUNC</gloss> coordination political and military implications <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> resistance armistice negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
